Package: SWORD
Type: Package
Title: Support Vector Machine Weighted Oblique Random Decision Forests
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-05-28
Authors@R: c(
    person("A.", "Carta",   role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "acarta88@yahoo.it",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4077-1822")),
    person("L.", "Frigau",  role = "aut"))
Description: Implements SWORD (Support vector machine Weighted Oblique Random
    Decision forests), a random forest of TORS (Tree Oblique for Regression
    with weighted SVM) oblique regression trees. At each internal node a
    Weighted-SVM classifier with a linear kernel defines the oblique splitting
    hyperplane as a sparse linear combination of predictors. The C++
    coordinate-descent solver provides fast training. Variable importance is
    computed via OIW-VI (Oblique Impurity-Weighted Variable Importance).
    Provides tree fitting (TORS), forest fitting (SWORD), prediction, and
    variable importance (VI_SWORD). Parallel tree fitting is supported via the
    'future'/'furrr' framework.
    The TORS algorithm is described in Carta and Frigau (2025)
    <doi:10.1007/s00180-025-01647-w>. The weighted SVM is based on
    Yang, Song and Cao (2005) <doi:10.1109/IJCNN.2005.1555965> and the
    'WeightSVM' package by Xu et al. (2024)
    <doi:10.32614/CRAN.package.WeightSVM>.
